American Singer/Actress, Lyric Bae teams up with US based Nigerian Artists, Tolu & J Lomah in the inspirational single, "E Go Beta" <img src="https://notjustok.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/egobeta-5.jpg"/> J Lomah, Tolu & Lyric Bae October 20, 2020 was a day that the world stood still. Lyric Bae, like many people, watched in horror as news reports came in of the shooting of peaceful protesters on that fateful night.How much is too much? Lyric made a decision to be impactful. She reached out to Tolu & J Lomah to make a song.The artists agreed to donate 40% of the streaming to benefit people struggling against injustice in Nigeria and other parts of Africa. This is their heartfelt collaboration. Watch the Official Video<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WPWhL52Z9b8" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0"></iframe> MORE ABOUT THE ARTISTSLYRIC BAELyric Bae is a singer, songwriter, actress and film producer from Texas, U.S.A. She effortlessly bridges the gaps between hip-hop and soul music with Afrobeat vibes TOLUTolu is a Nigerian singer, songwriter, recording artist, music producer, and actor. He was a finalist at the 2010 MTN Project Fame. He has worked with Don Jazzy & Tiwa Savage J LOMAHJLomah is a Nigerian singer and songwriter based in Dallas, TX. He combines both hustle and .talent to take the industry by storm. The post Lyric Bae teams up with Tolu & J Lomah in the inspirational single, "E Go Beta" appeared first on Most Trusted Voice in Music & Afrobeats from Nigeria & Africa | Notjustok. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.